# HLCA Project Implementation Plan

## Goal
Build the **Hybrid Lexicon-CyberBERT Abusive Content Reporting Algorithm (HLCA)** system as described in [HLCA.pdf](file:///c:/RADHEE/HLCA/HLCA.pdf). This system detects abusive content on webpages using a hybrid approach (Lexicon + BERT) and generates legally admissible forensic reports.

## Architecture
- **Chrome Extension**: Captures real-time text, DOM structure, and screenshots from the user's browser. Sends data to the backend.
- **Python Backend**:
    - **Preprocessing**: Homoglyph normalization, lemmatization.
    - **Lexicon Module**: Calculates Lexical Intensity Score (LIS).
    - **CyberBERT Module**: Uses a pre-trained BERT model for Contextual Abuse Score (CAS).
    - **Fusion Module**: Combines scores into Hybrid Confidence Score (HCS).
    - **Forensics Module**: Generates SHA-256 hashes and PDF/JSON reports.

## Proposed Changes (New Project)

### Directory Structure
```
c:\RADHEE\HLCA\
  ├── backend/
  │   ├── app.py              # Flask server
  │   ├── preprocessing.py    # Text normalization
  │   ├── lexicon.py          # LIS calculation
  │   ├── model.py            # CyberBERT (HuggingFace) integration
  │   ├── fusion.py           # HCS calculation
  │   ├── forensics.py        # Hashing and Report generation
  │   ├── requirements.txt    # Python dependencies
